The paper deals with logics for querying graph topology, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the intersection problem between regular and rational relations, which is a fundamental problem in automata theory and formal language theory, indicating that it could belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of regular and rational relations in lossy channel systems, which suggests that it could belong to the category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL). The paper also discusses the complexity of the intersection problem, which could place it in the category of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper mentions the classification of formulae based on their syntactic form, which could suggest that it belongs to the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM).
